{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Good morning. I think, as a grumpy Eastern European,"},{"time":5000,"text":"I was brought in to play the pessimist this morning. So bear with me."},{"time":9000,"text":"Well, I come from the former Soviet Republic of Belarus,"},{"time":12000,"text":"which, as some of you may know,"},{"time":15000,"text":"is not exactly an oasis of liberal democracy."},{"time":18000,"text":"So that's why I've always been fascinated"},{"time":22000,"text":"with how technology could actually reshape"},{"time":25000,"text":"and open up authoritarian societies like ours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"So, I'm graduating college"},{"time":30000,"text":"and, feeling very idealistic,"},{"time":32000,"text":"I decided to join the NGO"},{"time":34000,"text":"which actually was using new media"},{"time":36000,"text":"to promote democracy and media reform"},{"time":38000,"text":"in much of the former Soviet Union."},{"time":41000,"text":"However, to my surprise,"},{"time":43000,"text":"I discovered that dictatorships"},{"time":45000,"text":"do not crumble so easily."},{"time":47000,"text":"In fact, some of them actually"},{"time":50000,"text":"survived the Internet challenge,"},{"time":52000,"text":"and some got even more repressive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"So this is when I ran out of my idealism and"},{"time":58000,"text":"decided to quit my NGO job"},{"time":60000,"text":"and actually study how the Internet could impede democratization."},{"time":65000,"text":"Now, I must tell you that this was never"},{"time":67000,"text":"a very popular argument,"},{"time":70000,"text":"and it's probably not very popular yet"},{"time":72000,"text":"with some of you sitting in this audience."},{"time":74000,"text":"It was never popular with many political leaders,"},{"time":77000,"text":"especially those in the United States"},{"time":79000,"text":"who somehow thought that new media"},{"time":81000,"text":"would be able to do what missiles couldn't."},{"time":85000,"text":"That is, promote democracy in difficult places"},{"time":88000,"text":"where everything else has already been tried and failed."},{"time":92000,"text":"And I think by 2009,"},{"time":94000,"text":"this news has finally reached Britain,"},{"time":97000,"text":"so I should probably add Gordon Brown to this list as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100000,"text":"However, there is an underlying argument about logistics,"},{"time":105000,"text":"which has driven so much of this debate. Right?"},{"time":108000,"text":"So if you look at it close enough,"},{"time":110000,"text":"you'll actually see that much of this"},{"time":112000,"text":"is about economics."},{"time":115000,"text":"The cybertopians say, much like fax machines"},{"time":118000,"text":"and Xerox machines did in the '80s,"},{"time":121000,"text":"blogs and social networks"},{"time":123000,"text":"have radically transformed the economics of protest,"},{"time":126000,"text":"so people would inevitably rebel."},{"time":129000,"text":"To put it very simply,"},{"time":131000,"text":"the assumption so far has been"},{"time":133000,"text":"that if you give people enough connectivity,"},{"time":136000,"text":"if you give them enough devices,"},{"time":139000,"text":"democracy will inevitably follow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"And to tell you the truth,"},{"time":143000,"text":"I never really bought into this argument,"},{"time":146000,"text":"in part because I never saw three American presidents"},{"time":149000,"text":"agree on anything else in the past."},{"time":151000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":155000,"text":"But, you know, even beyond that,"},{"time":157000,"text":"if you think about the logic underlying it,"},{"time":159000,"text":"is something I call iPod liberalism,"},{"time":162000,"text":"where we assume that every single Iranian or Chinese"},{"time":166000,"text":"who happens to have and love his iPod"},{"time":168000,"text":"will also love liberal democracy."},{"time":172000,"text":"And again, I think this is kind of false."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"But I think a much bigger problem with this"},{"time":178000,"text":"is that this logic --"},{"time":180000,"text":"that we should be dropping iPods not bombs --"},{"time":183000,"text":"I mean, it would make a fascinating title"},{"time":186000,"text":"for Thomas Friedman's new book."},{"time":188000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":189000,"text":"But this is rarely a good sign. Right?"},{"time":193000,"text":"So, the bigger problem with this logic"},{"time":197000,"text":"is that it confuses the intended"},{"time":199000,"text":"versus the actual uses of technology."},{"time":203000,"text":"For those of you who think that"},{"time":205000,"text":"new media of the Internet"},{"time":207000,"text":"could somehow help us avert genocide,"},{"time":210000,"text":"should look no further than Rwanda,"},{"time":212000,"text":"where in the '90s it was actually two radio stations"},{"time":215000,"text":"which were responsible for fueling much of the ethnic hatred in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"But even beyond that, coming back to the Internet,"},{"time":222000,"text":"what you can actually see"},{"time":224000,"text":"is that certain governments"},{"time":226000,"text":"have mastered the use of cyberspace"},{"time":229000,"text":"for propaganda purposes. Right?"},{"time":231000,"text":"And they are building what I call the Spinternet."},{"time":233000,"text":"The combination of spin, on the one hand,"},{"time":236000,"text":"and the Internet on the other."},{"time":238000,"text":"So governments from Russia to China to Iran"},{"time":241000,"text":"are actually hiring, training and paying bloggers"},{"time":244000,"text":"in order to leave ideological comments"},{"time":247000,"text":"and create a lot of ideological blog posts"},{"time":249000,"text":"to comment on sensitive political issues. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":252000,"text":"So you may wonder, why on Earth are they doing it?"},{"time":256000,"text":"Why are they engaging with cyberspace?"},{"time":258000,"text":"Well my theory is that"},{"time":260000,"text":"it's happening because censorship actually"},{"time":263000,"text":"is less effective than you think it is in many of those places."},{"time":266000,"text":"The moment you put something critical in a blog,"},{"time":270000,"text":"even if you manage to ban it immediately,"},{"time":273000,"text":"it will still spread around thousands and thousands of other blogs."},{"time":277000,"text":"So the more you block it,"},{"time":279000,"text":"the more it emboldens people to actually avoid the censorship"},{"time":282000,"text":"and thus win in this cat-and-mouse game."},{"time":285000,"text":"So the only way to control this message"},{"time":289000,"text":"is actually to try to spin it"},{"time":291000,"text":"and accuse anyone who has written something critical"},{"time":294000,"text":"of being, for example, a CIA agent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296000,"text":"And, again, this is happening quite often."},{"time":299000,"text":"Just to give you an example of how it works in China, for example."},{"time":303000,"text":"There was a big case in February 2009"},{"time":307000,"text":"called \"Elude the Cat.\""},{"time":309000,"text":"And for those of you who didn't know, I'll just give a little summary."},{"time":313000,"text":"So what happened is that a 24-year-old man,"},{"time":316000,"text":"a Chinese man, died in prison custody."},{"time":319000,"text":"And police said that it happened"},{"time":322000,"text":"because he was playing hide and seek,"},{"time":324000,"text":"which is \"elude the cat\" in Chinese slang,"},{"time":327000,"text":"with other inmates and hit his head"},{"time":329000,"text":"against the wall,"},{"time":331000,"text":"which was not an explanation which sat well with many Chinese bloggers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"So they immediately began posting a lot of critical comments."},{"time":342000,"text":"In fact, QQ.com, which is a popular Chinese website,"},{"time":346000,"text":"had 35,000 comments"},{"time":348000,"text":"on this issue within hours."},{"time":350000,"text":"But then authorities did something very smart."},{"time":353000,"text":"Instead of trying to purge these comments,"},{"time":356000,"text":"they instead went and reached out to the bloggers."},{"time":359000,"text":"And they basically said, \"Look guys. We'd like you to become netizen investigators.\""},{"time":364000,"text":"So 500 people applied,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and four were selected to actually go and tour the facility in question,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and thus inspect it and then blog about it."},{"time":375000,"text":"Within days the entire incident was forgotten,"},{"time":378000,"text":"which would have never happened if they simply tried to block the content."},{"time":381000,"text":"People would keep talking about it for weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384000,"text":"And this actually fits with another interesting theory"},{"time":388000,"text":"about what's happening in authoritarian states"},{"time":391000,"text":"and in their cyberspace."},{"time":393000,"text":"This is what political scientists call authoritarian deliberation,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and it happens when governments are actually reaching out to their critics"},{"time":401000,"text":"and letting them engage with each other online."},{"time":403000,"text":"We tend to think"},{"time":405000,"text":"that somehow this is going to harm these dictatorships,"},{"time":408000,"text":"but in many cases it only strengthens them."},{"time":411000,"text":"And you may wonder why."},{"time":413000,"text":"I'll just give you a very short list of reasons"},{"time":415000,"text":"why authoritarian deliberation"},{"time":418000,"text":"may actually help the dictators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"And first it's quite simple."},{"time":422000,"text":"Most of them operate in a complete information vacuum."},{"time":425000,"text":"They don't really have the data they need"},{"time":428000,"text":"in order to identify emerging threats facing the regime."},{"time":431000,"text":"So encouraging people to actually go online"},{"time":434000,"text":"and share information and data"},{"time":436000,"text":"on blogs and wikis is great"},{"time":438000,"text":"because otherwise, low level apparatchiks and bureaucrats"},{"time":441000,"text":"will continue concealing what's actually happening in the country, right?"},{"time":445000,"text":"So from this perspective, having blogs and wikis"},{"time":447000,"text":"produce knowledge has been great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"Secondly, involving public in any decision making"},{"time":452000,"text":"is also great"},{"time":454000,"text":"because it helps you to share the blame"},{"time":456000,"text":"for the policies which eventually fail."},{"time":458000,"text":"Because they say, \"Well look, we asked you,"},{"time":460000,"text":"we consulted you, you voted on it."},{"time":462000,"text":"You put it on the front page of your blog."},{"time":464000,"text":"Well, great. You are the one who is to blame.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"And finally, the purpose of"},{"time":470000,"text":"any authoritarian deliberation efforts"},{"time":472000,"text":"is usually to increase the legitimacy of the regimes, both at home and abroad."},{"time":475000,"text":"So inviting people to all sorts of public forums,"},{"time":479000,"text":"having them participate in decision making,"},{"time":481000,"text":"it's actually great."},{"time":483000,"text":"Because what happens is that then"},{"time":485000,"text":"you can actually point to this initiative and say,"},{"time":487000,"text":"\"Well, we are having a democracy. We are having a forum.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":490000,"text":"Just to give you an example,"},{"time":492000,"text":"one of the Russian regions, for example,"},{"time":494000,"text":"now involves its citizens"},{"time":496000,"text":"in planning its strategy up until year 2020."},{"time":500000,"text":"Right? So they can go online"},{"time":502000,"text":"and contribute ideas on what that region would look like by the year 2020."},{"time":506000,"text":"I mean, anyone who has been to Russia would know"},{"time":508000,"text":"that there was no planning in Russia for the next month."},{"time":511000,"text":"So having people involved in planning for 2020"},{"time":514000,"text":"is not necessarily going to change anything,"},{"time":516000,"text":"because the dictators are still the ones who control the agenda."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"Just to give you an example from Iran,"},{"time":522000,"text":"we all heard about the Twitter revolution"},{"time":524000,"text":"that happened there,"},{"time":526000,"text":"but if you look close enough, you'll actually see"},{"time":528000,"text":"that many of the networks and blogs"},{"time":530000,"text":"and Twitter and Facebook were actually operational."},{"time":533000,"text":"They may have become slower,"},{"time":535000,"text":"but the activists could still access it"},{"time":537000,"text":"and actually argue that having access to them"},{"time":539000,"text":"is actually great for many authoritarian states."},{"time":542000,"text":"And it's great simply because"},{"time":545000,"text":"they can gather open source intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"In the past it would take you weeks, if not months,"},{"time":552000,"text":"to identify how Iranian activists connect to each other."},{"time":555000,"text":"Now you actually know how they connect to each other"},{"time":557000,"text":"by looking at their Facebook page."},{"time":559000,"text":"I mean KGB, and not just KGB,"},{"time":561000,"text":"used to torture in order to actually get this data."},{"time":564000,"text":"Now it's all available online."},{"time":566000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":568000,"text":"But I think the biggest conceptual pitfall"},{"time":570000,"text":"that cybertopians made"},{"time":572000,"text":"is when it comes to digital natives, people who have grown up online."},{"time":575000,"text":"We often hear about cyber activism,"},{"time":578000,"text":"how people are getting more active because of the Internet."},{"time":581000,"text":"Rarely hear about cyber hedonism, for example,"},{"time":583000,"text":"how people are becoming passive."},{"time":585000,"text":"Why? Because they somehow assume that the Internet"},{"time":587000,"text":"is going to be the catalyst of change"},{"time":589000,"text":"that will push young people into the streets,"},{"time":591000,"text":"while in fact it may actually be the new opium for the masses"},{"time":594000,"text":"which will keep the same people in their rooms downloading pornography."},{"time":597000,"text":"That's not an option being considered too strongly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"So for every digital renegade that is revolting in the streets of Tehran,"},{"time":604000,"text":"there may as well be two digital captives"},{"time":606000,"text":"who are actually rebelling only in the World of Warcraft."},{"time":609000,"text":"And this is realistic. And there is nothing wrong about it"},{"time":611000,"text":"because the Internet has greatly empowered many of these young people"},{"time":615000,"text":"and it plays a completely different social role for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"If you look at some of the surveys"},{"time":619000,"text":"on how the young people actually benefit from the Internet,"},{"time":622000,"text":"you'll see that the number of teenagers in China, for example,"},{"time":625000,"text":"for whom the Internet actually broadens their sex life,"},{"time":628000,"text":"is three times more than in the United States."},{"time":631000,"text":"So it does play a social role,"},{"time":633000,"text":"however it may not necessarily lead to political engagement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"So the way I tend to think of it"},{"time":638000,"text":"is like a hierarchy of cyber-needs in space,"},{"time":640000,"text":"a total rip-off from Abraham Maslow."},{"time":642000,"text":"But the point here is that"},{"time":644000,"text":"when we get the remote Russian village online,"},{"time":647000,"text":"what will get people to the Internet"},{"time":649000,"text":"is not going to be the reports from Human Rights Watch."},{"time":651000,"text":"It's going to be pornography, \"Sex and the City,\""},{"time":654000,"text":"or maybe watching funny videos of cats."},{"time":657000,"text":"So this is something you have to recognize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659000,"text":"So what should we do about it?"},{"time":661000,"text":"Well I say we have to stop thinking"},{"time":663000,"text":"about the number of iPods per capita"},{"time":666000,"text":"and start thinking about ways in which"},{"time":668000,"text":"we can empower intellectuals,"},{"time":671000,"text":"dissidents, NGOs and then the members of civil society."},{"time":674000,"text":"Because even what has been happening up 'til now"},{"time":677000,"text":"with the Spinternet and authoritarian deliberation,"},{"time":679000,"text":"there is a great chance that those voices will not be heard."},{"time":682000,"text":"So I think we should shatter some of our utopian assumptions"},{"time":685000,"text":"and actually start doing something about it."},{"time":687000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":689000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}